    {
      "href": "/acol_vida/list/suburban-malaise/",
      "user": "acol_vida",
      "slug": "suburban-malaise",
      "title": "Suburban Malaise",
      "desc": "The underlying darkness and punishing ennui of the suburban experience. Teen angst and middle aged mediocrity; malevolent boredom and dazed helplessness. The inevitable drag/march of time. Unrealised desires, overwrought emotions. Oh the crushing weight of contemporary life! Oh the banality of our entitled middle-class existence!\n\nAside from a few notable exceptions this list veers away from suburban horror and overt satire - no Nightmare on Elm St or Cry Baby: they feel like a different kind of film. Whilst there's a little \"weird suburbia\" here, it's usually tempered by that ineffable feeling of emotional disconnection and liminality that I've pulled under the banner of 'malaise'. Cheer up kid, next summer you can move to the city. That, or you'll be stuck here forever...",
      "owner": "List by Adam PATRON",
